The paper discusses clock synchronization in distributed systems, specifically in the context of Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) advertising. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a time synchronization service, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The paper also discusses error compensation mechanisms, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also utilizes low-level timestamping, which could fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of CheepSync on custom-designed platforms, which could fall under the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category.
